
allocPSA

Installation Guide 


1) System Requirements 
      MySQL >= 4 (although it _may_ work on 3.23) (Use /usr/sbin/mysqld -V for version)
      PHP   >= 4.3.0 (Try writing a php script with phpinfo(); in it to determine version)
      Ensure PHP register_globals enabled (/etc/php.ini)
      Ensure PHP memory_limit >= 64 meg (/etc/php.ini)
      Determine PHP include_path (/etc/php.ini)

2) Put the source code in the webserver document root 
      To determine the document root for Apache you could try something like 
      looking for the string DocumentRoot:
        find /etc/apache -iname "*.conf" -exec grep DocumentRoot {} \; | grep -v '#'
        find /etc/httpd -iname "*.conf" -exec grep DocumentRoot {} \; | grep -v '#'
      
      Alternatively determine the apache conf file from 
        apache2 -V | grep SERVER_CONFIG_FILE
        httpd -V | grep SERVER_CONFIG_FILE
      and then grep for DocumentRoot in the file

3) Fill in the values in /webroot/alloc/util/install.cfg

4) Run installer script /webroot/alloc/util/install.sh




